<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900817-0121</DOCNO><DOCID>900817-0121.</DOCID><HL>   Marketing andamp; Media:   Dow Jones to Stop   Using Bloomberg's   Distribution Service</HL><DATE>08/17/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B10</SO><CO>   DJ</CO><IN>MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)</IN><LP>   NEW YORK -- Dow Jones andamp; Co. said it would stopdistributing its newswires through Bloomberg L.P. starting inSeptember 1991.   Bloomberg distributes prices of financial instruments,including stocks and bonds, and provides analytic featuresthrough its terminals. About three months ago, Bloombergbegan a newswire, Bloomberg Business News, that carriescorporate news announcements, bond market coverage andforeign exchange reports, among other features.</LP><TEXT>   A Dow Jones spokesman said it acted under its longstandingpolicy against distributing its news services throughcompetitors. &quot;This decision has no bearing on ourrelationship with other vendors,&quot; he added.   Dow Jones also publishes The Wall Street Journal, Barron'smagazine, and community newspapers, and operates the TelerateInc. electronic financial information system.</TEXT></DOC>